    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of your tomato plants, a classic sign of trouble, are often a sign of a nutrient deficiency, like nitrogen, or perhaps overwatering. You can try gently loosening the soil around the base of the plants to see if roots are suffocating, which can be a major issue. If the soil is constantly soggy, let it dry out a bit between waterings—don't drown those poor roots! A balanced, slow-release fertilizer might also give your tomatoes the boost they need to perk up.",
